FBIS4-15193 "drsov067_a_94004" FBIS-SOV-94-067 Daily Report 6 Apr 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Phrase on Bases `Mistake' Phrase on Bases `Mistake' LD0604203394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1919 GMT 6 Apr 94 LD0604203394 Moscow INTERFAX English BFN [Text] Well-informed sources in Moscow say that the phrase about the formation of Russian military bases in CIS countries and Latvia was a result of an ambiguous expression that was later included in a Defense Ministry document and then copied to appropriate presidential statements. "This technical mistake is being corrected", the source in the Kremlin said adding that "there is no hidden political meaning behind it."
